Teva, Applisonix, Oil Refineries, Elad: Israel Equity Preview

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-04-07T06:29:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/teva-applisonix-oil-refineries-elad-israel-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Israeli markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
the company names and prices are from the last close unless
otherwise stated.  The TA-25 Index gained 0.6 percent to 1,335.10 in  Tel Aviv .  Applisonix Ltd. (APLS)  : The maker of long-term hair-
removal products received an Israeli patent for its hair removal
device and process. Applisonix dropped 1.3 percent to 0.673
shekel.  Delek Automotive Systems Ltd. (DLEA)  : The importer of
Mazda cars said it has several months of inventory available for
sale even though factories in Japan aren’t working at full
capacity after the earthquake. Delek slid 0.9 percent to 42.24
shekels.  Elad Canada Inc. (ELCN)  : Moody’s Midroog assigned an A2
rating to up to 300 million shekels of bonds ($87 million) the
real-estate company is considering offering. Elad was unchanged
at 12.31 shekels.  Jerusalem Oil Exploration (JOEL)  Ltd: The oil explorer
and property developer approved the appointment of Avi Geffen as
Chief Executive Officer. Jerusalem Oil rose 0.7 percent to 71.77
shekels.  Oil Refineries Ltd. (ORL)  : Israel’s Ministry of National
Infrastructures approved the flow of natural gas to the Haifa
facility of the country’s largest refiner. Oil Refineries
dropped 2.5 percent to 2.455 shekels.  Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. (TEVA)  : The world’s
largest maker of generic drugs said new clinical data provide
additional evidence to support the clinical potential of the
investigational compound custirsen to treat castrate resistant
prostate cancer. Teva increased 1 percent to 175.50 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in Tel Aviv at 
 swrobel4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
